	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Conway's Life simulator for NES</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><img src="http://nova.themonkeybob.net/rsc/conwayslife.png" alt="Image" /><br />Instead of trying to see how Video Life manages to be fast, I figured I would see how fast I could make a Life simulator by just using repetitive, fast code and using unofficial opcodes. It's pretty bare-bones so far and all you can do is move a cursor around to toggle cells and start/stop simulation, but I'm hoping to add onto it and have an option for a bigger grid because 32x32 isn't even big enough for the Gosper glider gun. SNES mouse support would also be cool, but I would require an emulator that both supports the mouse and doesn't choke on unofficial opcodes first.<br /><br /><a href="http://novasquirrel.com/dl/NESLife.zip" class="postlink">Download (with source)</a>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


